[[File:Mount Komekura Photovoltaic power plant Jan2012.JPG|thumb|upright=1.05|Part of the Solarpark]]

The '''Komekurayama Solar Power Plant''' (米倉山太陽光発電所) is a 10 [[megawatt]] (MW) solar [[photovoltaic power station]] located at Mt. Komekura.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/challenge/energy/megasolar/index-e.html Tepco real time monitor]</ref> It is the third solar plant built by [[Tokyo Electric Power Company|Tepco]], and was completed on January 27, 2012. In the first year of operation, it produced 14,434&nbsp;[[MWh]],<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/images/130130a.pdf Monthly Total]</ref> which was about 20% greater than anticipated.<ref>[http://www.tepco.co.jp/en/news/topics/1224458_2266.html The First Anniversary of Komekurayama Solar Power Station, a Mega Solar Power Station Located in Komekurayama, Yamanashi Prefecture]</ref>

