{{Italic title}} '''''Living in the Hothouse: How Global Warming Affects Australia''''' is a 2005 book by Professor [[Ian Lowe]] which is a sequel to his ''Living in the Greenhouse'' (1989). The book presents a detailed analysis of [[climate change]] science and the likely impact of [[climate change in Australia]]. ''Living in the Hothouse'' also offers a critical overview of the [[John Howard|Howard government]]'s policy response to climate change in Australia.<ref name=lowe>[http://home.vicnet.net.au/~abr/DecJan06/Eckersley%20review.htm Nothing but us] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070713112322/http://home.vicnet.net.au/~abr/DecJan06/Eckersley%20review.htm |date=July 13, 2007 }}</ref>
Ian Lowe, [[Order of Australia|AO]], is a scientist, environmental policy analyst, and president of the [[Australian Conservation Foundation]], who has served on many federal, state and local government committees.<ref name=lowe/>
Other books by Ian Lowe include ''[[Reaction Time (book)|Reaction Time]]'' and ''[[A Big Fix]]''.
